<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<entry xmlns:functx="http://www.functx.com" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_ala"
    xml:lang="os">
    <form type="lemma"><orth>ala</orth></form>
    <sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
            <q>копоть</q>
        </cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
            <q>soot</q>
        </cit></sense>
    <cit type="exampleGroup">
        <cit type="example">
            <quote>zamanajy ūrs wælʒarm xūd æxsævy cyraǧy ælajæ saw adardta</quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>отменно белая барашковая шапка за ночь почернела от копоти лучины</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>a superbly white Astrakhan cap turned black overnight from the soot of a
                    torch</q>
            </cit>
            <bibl><ref target="#src_F."/><biblScope>1957 III 30</biblScope></bibl>
        </cit>
        <cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
            <usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg>
            <quote>sirnik dær æj næ ǧæwuj, ala dær næ kænuj</quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>и спички ей (электрической лампочке) не нужно, и копоти не дает</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>and it (the light bulb) does not need a match, and does not produce soot</q>
            </cit>
            <bibl><ref target="#src_AK"/><biblScope>II 16</biblScope></bibl>
        </cit>
    </cit>
    <cit type="exampleGroup">
        <cit type="example">
            <quote>zamanajy ūrs wælʒarm xūd æxsævy cyraǧy ælajæ saw adardta</quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>отменно белая барашковая шапка за ночь почернела от копоти лучины</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>a superbly white Astrakhan cap turned black overnight from the soot of a
                    torch</q>
            </cit>
            <bibl><ref target="#src_F."/><biblScope>1957 III 30</biblScope></bibl>
        </cit>
        <cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
            <usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg>
            <quote>sirnik dær æj næ ǧæwuj, ala dær næ kænuj</quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>и спички ей (электрической лампочке) не нужно, и копоти не дает</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>and it (the light bulb) does not need a match, and does not produce soot</q>
            </cit>
            <bibl><ref target="#src_AK"/><biblScope>II 16</biblScope></bibl>
        </cit>
    </cit>
    <etym xml:lang="ru">Сближается с <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/><w>alæ</w></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>ali</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sva"
                ><lang/><w>hal</w><gloss><q>пламя</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ab"
                ><lang/><w>alwa</w><gloss><q>дым</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ab"
                ><w>alwaq</w><gloss><q>сажа</q></gloss></mentioned>, ; ср. также <mentioned
            xml:lang="av"><lang/><w>lah</w><gloss><q>сажа</q></gloss></mentioned>; можно
        предполагать связь перечисленных слов с <mentioned xml:lang="ar"
            ><lang/><w>ʽalaw</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="tr"
            ><lang/><w>alāw</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="tr"
                ><w>alew</w><gloss><q>пламя</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Связь с ос. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_arawyn"/> ‘палить’ мало вероятна, как и связь с <mentioned xml:lang="ine"
                ><lang/><w>*al</w><gloss><q>гореть</q></gloss></mentioned> (<mentioned xml:lang="tr"
                ><lang/><w>alāta-</w><gloss><q>головешка</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="tr"><w/><gloss><q>уголь</q></gloss></mentioned>, ).%n<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>312</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">Close to <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/><w>alæ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>ali</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sva"
                    ><lang/><w>hal</w><gloss><q>fire</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="ab"><lang/><w>alwa</w><gloss><q>smoke</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="ab"><w>alwaq</w><gloss><q>smoke-black</q></gloss></mentioned>, ; cf. also
            <mentioned xml:lang="av"><lang/><w>lah</w><gloss><q>smoke-black</q></gloss></mentioned>;
        it can be assumed that these words are related to <mentioned xml:lang="ar"
                ><lang/><w>ʽalaw</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="tr"
            ><lang/><w>alāw</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="tr"
                ><w>alew</w><gloss><q>fire</q></gloss></mentioned>, . The connection with Ossetic
            <ref type="xr" target="#entry_arawyn"/> ‘burn’ is unlikely, as well the connection with
            <mentioned xml:lang="ine"><lang/><w>*al</w><gloss><q>burn</q></gloss></mentioned>
            (<mentioned xml:lang="tr"
            ><lang/><w>alāta-</w><gloss><q>firebrand</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="tr"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>coal</q></gloss></mentioned>, ).%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                /><biblScope>312</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
</entry>
